The rice is super moist and flavorful! The service is A1, the roast pork is tasty, sticky and flavor packed. The stewed chicken is stewed in an ingredient rich tomato broth. The sweet plantains are cooked to perfection and have the perfect balance between sweet and tangy. The salad was crisp, fresh and complimented the food. My daughter ordered a large (can serve 2) coconut fountain drink. It too was delicious! This is my second time eating here, I have a very discriminating palate when it comes to carribean food and I am pleasantly surprised by this place.

I called on a Sunday to order food and had me on hold for a half an hour then I figured I'd hang up and call again and the line was busy because they still had my call on hold. Ok I gave them another shot today and I called to order food for me to pick up and they seemed happy about me picking up my own food. In the time I walked from my home to this establishment it should be done. Nope when I got there a lady knew about my phone order mind you there's six people working and it's not busy and they all took four people ahead of me, how fair is that. I was trying to keep my composure and I told the lady I made an order through the phone where is my bagged food so that I can take my food to go and pay. She says oh yeah and begins to prepare my food. I am never coming here again. They all looked right at me and no one bothered to help me and the lady who knew about my order because she asked me , decided to make other people who came in after me a priority. This place lacks customer service or they have favorites all in all I think that's bull.
